The paper presents a technique for specifying trigger-action todo comments as executable statements, which is relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the evaluation of the technique in terms of cost, which could fall under software development (cs.SD). Additionally, the paper involves the use of abstract syntax trees, which could relate to machine learning (cs.LG) or cybernetics (cs.CY).
